20/03/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska's government scrambled Wednesday (19 March) to come up with 1.1m euros, needed to pay back wages owed employees in the higher education, cultural and scientific sectors. 
Workers from over 100 institutions in the Bosnian Serb entity went on strike, demanding money owed them since December.
Also Wednesday, Stability Pact for South Eastern Europe Special Co-ordinator Erhard Busek ended his three-day visit to Sarajevo. 
He announced that the headquarters of the Pact's initiative for fighting organised crime would be located in the city, as requested by High Representative Paddy Ashdown. 
(OHR Sources - 20/03/03; RTRS, NTV Hayat, PBS BiH - 19/03/03)
